public class FirstAgent
extends java.lang.Object
implements ch.idsia.agents.Agent

FirstAgent is an Agent that looks at its environment and decides which action is best using a predetermined list of what to do when.

getAction

public boolean[] getAction()
Used to return the required actions to the game.

Specified by:
getAction in interface ch.idsia.agents.Agent
Returns:
boolean array of size 6. Each element in the array represents a movement: true indicates it is being requested during this frame & false means it is not. From 0 to 5 the corresponding movements are: left, right, down, jump, speed, up.
See Also:
Agent.getAction()

integrateObservation

public void integrateObservation(ch.idsia.benchmark.mario.environments.Environment environment)
Used to update the Agent with information about the environment. This gets called by the game every frame & passes the updated Environment to the Agent to allow it to update its knowledge of the world (such as where remaining enemies, coins and blocks are).

Specified by:
integrateObservation in interface ch.idsia.agents.Agent
Parameters:
environment - containing updated knowledge

giveIntermediateReward

public void giveIntermediateReward(float intermediateReward)
Used to tell Mario when he has done a good move & when he hasn't. Examples: Increases if coins, mushrooms or hidden blocks are collected; or if enemies are stomped on. Decreases if you collide with an enemy.

Specified by:
giveIntermediateReward in interface ch.idsia.agents.Agent
